Communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

[There is also a report in the Concord Monitor:
<http://www.concordmonitor.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20100128/NEWS01/128
0332/1001/NEWS01>, but it gives nothing not in either of the above reports.

From enquiries, one of the 2 positive drums was probably the source,
and, interestingly, it had been in use for some 10 years without any
problems. The present environmental contamination is minimal.
Somehow, spores got into this young lady's mouth and were swallowed.
It may be that a key factor is that she had a hookworm infection, and
the mucosal damage from this parasite feeding allowed spore entry
into the intestinal tissues. She was singularly unlucky. Fortunately,
when she presented herself with abdominal symptoms at the local
emergency clinic, they took a blood sample. Like many I expect, I
look forward to the full report when it is published. - Mod.MHJ]
